                  </persName>
            . I stopped the prisoner with all the things mentioned in the indictment in Shoreditch, on the 13th of January; he gave several<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177502180048"></xptr> different accounts how he came by them; I took him to justice Wilmot's, Smith was at the justices that night, when he was committed.</p>
               <p>The things were produced and deposed to by the prosecutors.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I met a carpenter, who asked me to dispose of these things for him.</p>
